[This case points out the need to take a good travel history in order to include tropical diseases in rule outs for a definitive diagnosis when patients fall ill on return to their temperate zone homes. Although there is no possibility of ongoing transmission of chikungunya virus in Germany, this case should serve as an alert for health care providers who advise travelers going to chikungunya virus endemic areas to avoid mosquito bites. Since Bali is a major tourist destination, any outbreak could have a negative impact on tourism.

ProMED-mail thanks Drs Wolfel, Vollmar, and Poluda for this first-hand report.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map showing the location of Bali can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1oOH. - Mod.TY]
